The paper deals with the blind estimation of massive MIMO channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the exploitation of sparsity in the angular domain, which is a key property of the channels, and this is a topic that falls under the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with the separation of interfering users from adjacent base stations, which is a topic that falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance limit based on the Cram\'er Rao lower bound, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
